headline: Norfolk Southern (NSC): Buy, Sell, or Hold Post Q2 Earnings?
summary: Norfolk Southern has had an impressive run over the past six months as its shares have beaten the S&P 500 by 5.2%. The stock now trades at $280.02, marking a 10.5% gain. This performance may have investors wondering how to approach the situation.
